    title: "MBSA Evaluations",
    start: '2024-03-02T14:30',
    end: '2024-03-02T18:30:01',
    description: '<h3>Spring 2024 Season</h3><h5>Location: Gateway Auxiliary Gym 2:30 - 6:30pm</h5><p><img class="alignnone wp-image-2492 size-full" src="/media/2024/02/Screenshot-2024-02-28-at-12.44.00 AM.png" alt="" width="1254" height="466" /></p><h5 style="text-align: left;">Our annual evaluations are here!  Time sure does fly when you’re having fun!  Please review the table above for your players division/time to report for evaluations in preparation for the upcoming draft.  This is the time where coaches will evaluate registered players to ensure we evenly distribute talent across teams to generate competitive game play throughout the season. </h5><p>Upon arrival families should “check in” at the entry desk.  Players will be given a number and then may enter the gym to begin stretching/warming up.  If you have requested your player “play up” this is an opportunity for that evaluation to occur.  Please arrive at your regularly scheduled time and let the entry personnel know you want your player to be evaluated for movement. </p><p>Head coaches will be notified shortly.  The MBSA Spring Draft will be held on Thursday, March 7th.  Additional details on the draft will come out soon to the head coaches of each division.  The drafts for softball will be led by MBSA Softball Commissioner, Jeff Kovacs, and baseball will be overseen by MBSA Executive Commissioner, Josh Plassmeyer.   If anyone has any questions regarding the drafts please email us at<span style="color: #0000ff;"> </span><a href="mailto:softball@mbsagators.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="color: #0000ff;">softball@mbsagators.com</span></a> or <a href="mailto:commissioner@mbsagators.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="color: #0000ff;">commissioner@mbsagators.com</span></a>. </p><p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Softball Announcement</span> - We will have special guests assisting with our evaluations on Saturday.  The Gateway High School softball team will join us to help run our drills! </p><p><span style="color: #ff0000;">Instructional and 6U Softball Families</span> - will have a standard clinic and not have official evaluations for these age groups.<br /><u><br /><span style="color: #ff0000;">Coaches for both leagues should attend their designated session for evaluations.  If you are unable to make it please let the corresponding commissioner know in advance.  Players are not required but it is highly recommended that they attend so that we can properly balance the teams during our draft night on March 7<sup>th</sup>.</span></u></p><p>All coaches should confirm that MBSA has clearances in place prior to starting practice in March.  Please follow the link below to get those documents started as some take a little time to come in.  Once the certificates are received please email them to <a href="mailto:info@mbsagators.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><span style="color: #0000ff;">info@mbsagators.com</span></a>.</p><h5 style="text-align: left;" align="center"><span style="color: #0000ff;"><a style="color: #0000ff;" href="https://mbsagators.com/coaches/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://mbsagators.com/coaches/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1709213233247000&amp;usg=AOvVaw11Aj3J31FvoeReEc35dFG1">https://mbsagators.com/<wbr />coaches</a></span></h5><h5 style="text-align: left;" align="center">Please keep an eye on your emails!  Make sure that our account is set to not be forwarded to junk or spam folders!  This is our most effective form of communication!  The website will be updated regularly with any new information, but emails are the best and most timely source of information! </h5><p>We look forward to amazing start of our Spring Season!  Go Gators!</p><p>See you on the fields,</p><h5 style="text-align: left;"> </h5><h5 style="text-align: left;">MBSA Board of Directors</h5>',
