    description: '<p><strong>Coaches "Clinic" and Tutorial</strong><br /><br />The Commissioners of MBSA, Josh Plassmeyer and Jeff Kovacs, will be hosting a Coaches Expectations and GameChanger Tutorial Session during each of the times noted below.  We HIGHLY encourage all coaches both Head and Assistant to attend.   During this session Jeff will review the basic of GameChanger as all teams must use this app moving forward for management of teams.  Josh and Jeff will review the Coaches Expectations as we begin our spring season.  This will include review of how best to approach Spring practices, planning, and much more.  Jeff will show the ins and outs of player entry, game score keeping, and messaging basics during this time.<br /><br />We are excited to announce the return of our <strong>Speed and Agility clinic with GAMA /Forza Sports &amp; Performance Training</strong>.<br /><br /><u>When:</u>  Saturday March 16th<br /><br /><u>Where:</u> Gateway High School Auxiliary Gym<br /><br /><u>Times:</u>        3:30 - 4:30pm - 7-8 year olds</p><p>                   4:30 - 5:30pm - 9-10 year olds</p><p>                   5:30 - 6:30pm - 11-14 year olds</p><p><br />These clinics are co-ed and designed to help everyone learn basic skills and drills to improve their speed and agility and safety while playing sports.<br /><br />GAMA and Forza Sports and Performance Training has been a very strong partner of MBSA since we first started last year.  They have offered field time, clinics, assessments, etc to our organization. We really appreciate their will and drive to mirror our goal of getting the youth of MBSA active and on the fields!<br /><br /><u>Instructional T-ball and 6U Clinic</u><br /><br />Our regularly scheduled Instructional Clinic will continue at the Gateway High School Auxiliary Gym from 2:30-3:30 on March 16th too!</p><p><br />Registration for both events can be found on our website: <a href="http://www.mbsagators.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=http://www.mbsagators.com&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1710177412492000&amp;usg=AOvVaw3_4Csody_2KDazQxlv0B49">www.mbsagators.com</a>.<br /><br />See you on the fields,<br /><br />MBSA Board of Directors</p>',
